{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981820124,"sessionID":"ses_1cc6c7f43ffeysIKN6y6Fy7ITJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_NXb0rUd9AkKJ21QlggwvgAsw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"neurectoderm|neuroectoderm","path":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon","include":"*.{obo,owl,md,txt,tsv,json,yaml}"},"output":"Found 800 matches (showing first 100)\n/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json:\n  Line 2:   \"body\": \"The term UBERON:0002346 \\\"neurectoderm\\\" also has a synonym \\\"neuroectoderm.\\\" However, neuroectoderm seems more common amongst the linked cross references, and I also see more results when exact searching Pubmed for neuroectoderm. Are there any reasons why neurectoderm is preferred by UBERON over neuroectoderm?\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n\n  Line 20:   \"title\": \"UBERON:0002346 \\\"neurectoderm\\\" vs \\\"neuroectoderm\\\"\",\n\n\n/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__pr_result__/uberon.obo:\n  Line 13846: def: \"A non-terminally differentiated cell that develops form the neuroectoderm. Glioblast has the potential to differentiate into various types of glial cells, including astrocytes and oligodendrocytes.\" [PMID:37824650, Wikipedia:Glioblast]\n\n  Line 13850: relationship: develops_from CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 14030: def: \"An undifferentiated neural cell that originates from the neuroectoderm and has the capacity both to perpetually self-renew without differentiating and to generate multiple central nervous system neuronal and glial cell types.\" [PMID:30639325]\n\n  Line 14039: relationship: develops_from CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 14254: def: \"A neuroepithelial glial cell, derived from a radial glial cell originating from the neuroectoderm, lines the ventricles of the brain and the central canal of the spinal cord. This cell is characterized by the presence of cilia on its apical surface, which can be motile or non-motile.\" [doi:/10.3389/fncel.2021.703951, GOC:tfm, https://www.britannica.com/science/ependymal-cell, JB:jb, PMID:34335193, PMID:37008045, PMID:9550134]\n\n  Line 14554: relationship: develops_from CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 14858: name: neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 14861: synonym: \"neurectoderm cell\" EXACT []\n\n  Line 18208: intersection_of: develops_from CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 18209: relationship: develops_from CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 22821: def: \"A circular smooth muscle cell of the iris, innervated by the ciliary nerves (parasympathetic), and acting to contract the pupil. This muscle cell derives from neuroectoderm. This smooth muscle cell results from transformation of epithelial cells to smooth muscle cells.\" [GOC:tfm, ISBN:0721662544, ISBN:0721694128]\n\n  Line 22830: relationship: develops_from CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 25714: relationship: develops_from CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 25972: relationship: develops_from CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 33098: comment: Cellular functions and extracellular interactions of choroidal melanocytes are distinct to skin melanocytes. They might have both neuroectodermal as well as mesectodermal origins. {xref=\"PMID:34082079\", xref=\"PMID:31819095\"}\n\n  Line 44031: def: \"The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the optic vesicle from the lateral wall of the forebrain. This process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the vesicle and ends when the vesicle has evaginated. The optic vesicle is the evagination of neurectoderm that precedes formation of the optic cup.\" [GOC:ascb_2009, GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n\n  Line 44045: def: \"The developmental process pertaining to the formation and shaping of the optic vesicle. This process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the vesicle and ends when the vesicle has evaginated. The optic vesicle is the evagination of neurectoderm that precedes formation of the optic cup.\" [GOC:ascb_2009, GOC:dph, GOC:tb]\n\n  Line 55648: def: \"The formation of a solid rod of neurectoderm derived from the neural keel. The neural rod is roughly circular in cross section. Neural rod formation occurs during primary neurulation in teleosts.\" [GOC:dh, GOC:ef]\n\n  Line 55659: def: \"The formation of a thickened region of the neurectoderm that is roughly triangular in cross section. The neural keel develops from the neural plate and develops into the neural rod. Neural keel formation occurs during primary neurulation in teleosts.\" [GOC:dh, GOC:ef]\n\n  Line 97680: def: \"The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a camera-type eye from unspecified neurectoderm. This process begins with the differentiation of cells that form the optic field and ends when the optic cup has attained its shape.\" [GOC:dph, GOC:sdb_2009, GOC:tb]\n\n  Line 153119: def: \"The pituitary gland is an endocrine gland that secretes hormones that regulate many other glands [GO]. An endocrine gland located ventral to the diencephalon and derived from mixed neuroectodermal and non neuroectodermal origin [ZFIN].\" [Wikipedia:Pituitary_gland, ZFIN:curator]\n\n  Line 153186: property_value: external_definition \"An endocrine gland located ventral to the diencephalon and derived from mixed neuroectodermal and non neuroectodermal origin.[TAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-08-14\", external_class=\"TAO:0000118\", ontology=\"TAO\", source=\"ZFIN:curator\"}\n\n  Line 155156: def: \"The surface (external) layer of ectoderm which begins to proliferate shortly after separation from the neuroectoderm.\" [MGI:anna, MP:0012532]\n\n  Line 155177: relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 155182: property_value: editor_note \"merge with non-neural. In vertebrates, the ectoderm has three parts: external ectoderm (also known as surface ectoderm), the neurectoderm (neural crest, and neural tube)\" xsd:string\n\n  Line 162957: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 182862: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 {source=\"ISBN:0781772214\"} ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 182909: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 {source=\"ISBN:0781772214\"} ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 188588: property_value: development_notes \"Majority derives from NC that surrounds optic cup of neurectoderm; a small temporal portion develops from the mesoderm that contributes to striated extra-ocular muscles and vascular endothelia[Rada&Johnson].\" xsd:string\n\n  Line 188662: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 {source=\"ISBN:0781772214\"} ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 189540: relationship: has_developmental_contribution_from UBERON:0002346 {notes=\"neural ectoderm of optic cup\", source=\"ISBN:0781772214\"} ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 192542: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 192603: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 192704: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 192786: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 197738: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 203764: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 208128: relationship: part_of UBERON:0002346 {source=\"XAO\", source=\"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/wiki/The-neural-crest\"} ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 208184: name: neurectoderm\n\n  Line 208190: synonym: \"epithelium tubi neuralis; neuroectoderma\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Neuroectoderm]\n\n  Line 208193: synonym: \"neuroectoderm\" EXACT []\n\n  Line 208218: relationship: has_part CL:0000133 ! neurectodermal cell\n\n  Line 208219: property_value: has_relational_adjective \"neurectodermal\" xsd:string\n\n  Line 208221: property_value: terminology_notes \"we prefer neurectoderm to neural ectoderm since placodal ectoderm is not classified here\" xsd:string\n\n  Line 227697: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 247856: def: \"The optic vesicle is the evagination of neurectoderm that precedes formation of the optic cup[GO]. Portion of tissue that is comprised of neuroepitheium which has pinched off from the anterior neural keel and will form the optic cup[ZFA].\" [GO:0003404, Wikipedia:Optic_vesicles]\n\n  Line 247881: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 {source=\"GO-def\"} ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 265319: def: \"A solid rod of neurectoderm derived from the neural keel. The neural rod is roughly circular in cross section. Neural rod formation occurs during primary neurulation in teleosts[GO]. An intermediate stage in the development of the central nervous system present during the segmentation period; the neural rod is roughly cylindrical in shape, forms from the neural keel, and is not yet hollowed out into the neural tube[ZFIN].\" [GO:0014024, ZFA:0000133]\n\n  Line 272922: relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 272925: property_value: homology_notes \"In the early gastrula of vertebrates, factors from the organizer (e.g. noggin, chordin, and follistatin in Xenopus) antagonize the epidermalizing factor bone morphogenetic protein 4 (BMP4), thus dividing the epiblast into neuroectoderm. In Drosophila, decapentaplegic, the homologue of BMP4, interacts similarly with the protein short gastrulation, the homologue of chordin. Thus, a comparable molecular mechanism for distinguishing non-neural ectoderm from neural ectoderm was probably present in the common ancestor of all bilaterally symmetrical animals.[well established][VHOG]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-09-17\", external_class=\"VHOG:0001372\", ontology=\"VHOG\", source=\"DOI:10.1016/S0959-4388(99)00003-3 Holland LZ and Holland ND, Chordate origins of the vertebrate central nervous system. Current Opinion in Neurobiology (1999)\", source=\"http://bgee.unil.ch/\"}\n\n  Line 282002: relationship: part_of UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 294693: synonym: \"prospective neuroectoderm\" EXACT [ZFA:0000063]\n\n  Line 294701: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 308861: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 350061: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 355683: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:7742\"} ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 370392: def: \"The outgrowth of neuroectoderm located on the floor of the embryonic hypothalamus that gives rise to the neurohypophysis (posterior lobe) of the pituitary gland.\" [https://sourceforge.net/p/obo/mammalian-phenotype-requests/1930/, MP:0013339]\n\n  Line 416768: def: \"An equivalence group of the neurectoderm where all cells can, although only one will, become a neural progenitor cell.\" [FlyBase:FBrf0074477, FlyBase:FBrf0089570]\n\n  Line 418154: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n\n/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__pr_result__/uberon-with-isa.obo:\n  Line 2771: def: \"The pituitary gland is an endocrine gland that secretes hormones that regulate many other glands [GO]. An endocrine gland located ventral to the diencephalon and derived from mixed neuroectodermal and non neuroectodermal origin [ZFIN].\" [ZFIN:curator, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pituitary_gland]\n\n  Line 4490: def: \"The surface (external) layer of ectoderm which begins to proliferate shortly after separation from the neuroectoderm.\" [MGI:anna, MP:0012532]\n\n  Line 28748: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 28787: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 33786: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 34557: relationship: has_developmental_contribution_from UBERON:0002346 ! neurectoderm\n\n  Line 46938: relationship: develops_from UBER